body:
## 🐛 Bug Report

I have a project in which i loop through an array of objects, create a sheet for each object and a table with some data in the sheet. The issue arises when opening the generated excel. It opens in protected view and all the data validations that i have placed get erased in the restoration process.

When creating the sheets and tables manually (not through the loop), it works fine.

The error that appears when opening the excel:
![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2aa9439f-736b-4e2e-b27e-b331852c433c)

Lib version: 4.4.0

## Steps To Reproduce

this is the code that gets executed when i access my projects backend:

const currentState = async () => {
  const workbook = new exceljs.Workbook();
  const buildings = await findAllBuilding();

  buildings.map((building: Building) => {
    addTable(building, workbook);
  });

  return workbook;
};

and the function addTable looks like this:

export const addTable = (building: Building, workbook: exceljs.Workbook) => {
  const sheet = workbook.addWorksheet(`${building._id}`);
  sheet.properties.defaultColWidth = 14.5;
  sheet.views = [{ rightToLeft: true }];
  sheet.addTable({
    name: 'rooms',
    ref: "A1",
    headerRow: true,
    style: {
      theme: "TableStyleMedium9",
      showRowStripes: true,
    },
    columns: [
      { name: "buildingID", filterButton: true },
      { name: "compound", filterButton: false },
      { name: "apartmentNumber", filterButton: true },
      { name: "residentNumber", filterButton: true },
      { name: "fullName", filterButton: true },
      { name: "Gender", filterButton: true },
      { name: "Section", filterButton: true },
      { name: "Population", filterButton: true },
    ],
    rows: [[]],
  });
};

the function doesn't do any insertions to the table right now due to it not working even in its current state.

## The expected behaviour:

the expectation is that when generating the sheets and tables the excel should be valid and not require repairing.
